C. Itoh and Co Ltd &lt;CITT.T> said its groupnet profit in the year ending March 31, 1988, is expected to beunchanged from a year earlier.    The prediction assumes a yen/dollar rate of 140 yen and acrude oil price of 18 dlrs a barrel, a company spokesman toldReuters. Sales in 1987/88 are estimated at 15,100 billion yen,up 2.3 pct from a year earlier.    The company earlier reported group net profit of 20.07billion yen in the year ended March 31, 1987, up 8.6 pct from ayear earlier, helped by a drop in sales and administrationcosts and reduced interest charges. REUTER&#3;